## Visual identity

### Art direction

The brand art establishes the aesthetic ceiling. Every visual asset should feel like it belongs in the same animated feature film — rendered chickens, warm cinematic lighting, dramatic sky, motion blur, feathers mid-air. The reference is Pixar-level production value applied to the most unserious subject possible.

Key visual ingredients from the brand art:
- Foreground hero chicken: large, muscular, angry, red comb, wide open beak, charging directly at camera
- Army of chickens behind: same energy, same direction, same rage
- Lighting: golden hour / sunset, light source directly behind the hero, strong rim light on feathers
- Sky: deep purple-blue to warm orange gradient, dramatic clouds, feathers floating
- Ground: green grass, dust kicked up, motion and urgency
- Background: wooden coop structure visible on the right — the thing they came from, now left behind

Everything that follows the brand art (merch, social posts, marketing materials) should feel like stills from this world.

