## The egg points system

Points are called **eggs**. They are earned by participating on the platform and will be used for the $COOP token airdrop.

### Earning eggs

| Action | Eggs earned |
|---|---|
| Contribute 1 SOL to a presale | 100 eggs |
| Lay an egg (create a presale) | 500 eggs |
| Claim LP trading fees | 25 eggs per claim |
| Refer a chicken who contributes | 200 eggs per referral |
| Hold a hatched token (weekly snapshot) | 10 eggs per token held |

### Display rules

- Always show eggs with the egg icon (the small oval shape from the platform UI), never just a number alone.
- Egg count in the nav: "482 eggs" — lowercase, always.
- In congratulatory moments: "You just earned 100 eggs" — present tense, direct.
- Never say "points." Always "eggs."

### Airdrop narrative

The framing: **you are not earning points. you are building your flock.** The more eggs you hold, the bigger your claim in the $COOP airdrop. Chickens who hatched the most eggs run the coop.

